        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 19 at 4:23PM EDT by NWS Wilmington OH</headline>
        <description>At 422 PM EDT, a cluster of strong thunderstorms were located along a
line extending from near New Madison to near Trotwood, moving
northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph, frequent cloud-to-ground
lightning, and torrential rainfall.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Lightning can cause serious injury or
death. Visibility will be poor and hydroplaning is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Dayton, Huber Heights, Troy, Trotwood, Piqua, Vandalia, Englewood,
Greenville, Tipp City, West Milton, Versailles, Covington, Arcanum,
Bradford, Lewisburg, Pleasant Hill, New Madison, Brown, Riverside,
and Clayton.

This includes the following Interstates...
I-70 in Ohio between mile markers 11 and 38.
I-75 in Ohio between mile markers 57 and 86.

Motorists should slow down and use extra caution.

When thunder roars, go indoors! Do not stay in the open or seek
shelter under trees when lightning threatens.

To report hazardous weather conditions, go to our website at
weather.gov/iln and submit your report via social media, when you can
do so safely.
</description>
